<p><a href="https://www.bigmarker.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">BigMarker</a> is a browser-based software for webinars, videos and online summits. The software is used by major corporations like Google, Nielsen, McDonalds, and Panasonic.</p>
<p><strong>Pros: </strong>BigMarker offers customizable, branded video forms with interactive elements like polls, surveys and offers that appear right next to the presentation. You can also connect streams with multiple cameras seamlessly to Facebook and <a href="/blog/ws/2020/04/27/youtube-live">YouTube Live</a>.</p>
<p><strong>Cons: </strong>BigMarker can be expensive to scale. Itâ€™s also a little less intuitive for attendees to navigate depending on how your webinar is set up. Marketers should strike a balance between a simple webinar and one with flashy interactive elements. You donâ€™t want to overwhelm your attendees.</p>
<p><strong>Pricing: </strong>Plans range from $79-299/mo for up to 1,000 attendees. Enterprise plans are available.</p>
<h3>Best webinar platform #12: Livestorm</h3>
<div class="embedded-entity align-center" data-embed-button="images" data-entity-embed-display="view_mode:media.simple_image" data-entity-type="media" data-entity-uuid="eb5f7ee3-fb70-42d4-a2ba-dd60e2bdf4ca" data-langcode="en">
