</article>
</div>
<p class="text-align-center"><em><a href="https://livestorm.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Image source</a></em></p>
<p><a href="https://livestorm.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Livestorm</a> positions itself as a â€œvideo communication toolâ€ that can be used to produce high-quality webinars to engage prospects. If youâ€™re in a hurry, Livestorm is for you.</p>
<p><strong>Pros: </strong>The platform automates the building of registration pages, reminders and basic webinar infrastructure, making it easy for you to go from idea to reality. It has nearly 30 integrations and also offers trigger automations that you can set to play videos or go to a new slide after a predetermined amount of time.</p>
<p><strong>Cons: </strong>Livestormâ€™s main negative is the amount of participants it allows in the webinar at one time for some of their smaller plans.</p>
<p><strong>Pricing: </strong>Prospects can try out Livestormâ€™s free plan to test the product. Their $99/month plan allows up to 100 participants in a webinar at once.</p>
<h2>Which webinar platform is the best for your business?</h2>
<p>As with any type of software, the best webinar platform for your company depends on your objectives, budget, and strategy.</p>
<h3>Best webinar platforms for entrepreneurs</h3>
<p>If youâ€™re just looking to try out a webinar or two, consider the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2014/10/01/marketing-ideas-for-small-businesses">low-cost options</a> of Livestorm, BigMarker or ClickMeeting.</p>
<h3>Best webinar platforms for startups</h3>
