<p>Here are just some of the ways you can use personalized video marketing strategies for your business, and weâ€™ve identified the strategies that might work better for B2B or B2C.</p>
<h3>1. Event invites</h3>
<p>When youâ€™re planning your next eventâ€”whether itâ€™s an online tutorial, webinar, or product launchâ€”we recommend that you lean heavily on video personalization.</p>
<p>Hereâ€™s why: Personalized event invite emails have led to an <a href="https://marketingland.com/5-ways-use-personalized-video-next-marketing-campaign-193064" target="_blank" rel="noopener">8x</a> improvement on click-through rates<strong>. </strong>When Marketo used personalized video marketing to invite attendees to an event, they saw a <a href="https://www.vidyard.com/customers/marketo-video-enabled-business-case-study/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">36%</a> increase in open rates.</p>
<h3>2. Explainer videos</h3>
<p>This could work for both B2B and B2C companies, but itâ€™s a particularly great strategy for B2Bs. An explainer video is a great way for a B2B company to talk directly to a prospect and explain or distill what makes the B2Bâ€™s service stand out. More than that, an explainer video is a tool a B2B business can use to show a prospect how their service can help.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.socialmediatoday.com/news/video-marketing-statistics-for-2020-infographic/566099/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">72%</a> of customers prefer to learn about a product through video. Thatâ€™s a great reason to start explaining in personalized videos.</p>
<h3>3. Case study videos</h3>
<p>A case study is a way to boost your credibility. Itâ€™s a blueprint of how you achieved success for a previous client. Yet, the beauty of a case study is that no one reads them and thinks, â€œletâ€™s just steal this idea,â€ because the execution is as important as the strategy.</p>
<p>What a good case study does is highlight your companyâ€™s strategic mindset, and show that you know how to measure value.</p>
<p>Case studies can also be long and boring. But converting your tired case study into video is a major win for your customer.</p>
