<p>Letâ€™s face it: Your competitors are likely doing what youâ€™re doingâ€”cold pitching, offering promotions for new customers, and other aggressive marketing tactics.</p>
<p>The best defense is a good offense.</p>
<p>In our experience, touching base with a new customer just once isnâ€™t enough but we recommend you start with two different videos.</p>
<p><em>The first video will be a simple thank you video. </em>This is where you can take your new customerâ€™s information (their name, their business, what their business does, how theyâ€™ll use your service), and automatically upload it into a video template and send it.</p>
<p>This lets your company show appreciation while treating your new customer as an individual.</p>
<p><em>The second video can now be more instructional. </em>Depending on what youâ€™re selling, there could be multiple levels or tiers of services, or multiple uses for a single product. There can also be some confusion on your customerâ€™s end on how to best use your product.</p>
<p>Have a series of videos that walk your new customer through how your service can benefit their business.</p>
<h3>5. Facebook ads</h3>
